This is another example
from the southern India in neaby Chenai.

132
00:08:10,205 --> 00:08:14,197
You see this hut with a thatched roof.

133
00:08:14,602 --> 00:08:19,258
Inside are these cement bins
with vermicomposting.

134
00:08:19,258 --> 00:08:26,119
What you can also see is this grid, 
this mesh that covers the worm bins

135
00:08:26,119 --> 00:08:27,881
to keep predators out.

136
00:08:29,687 --> 00:08:35,723
Finally, also a larger example from the US
with these automized vermi bins.

137
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:38,109
This has an automatic feeding

138
00:08:38,579 --> 00:08:43,372
and it also has an automatic 
harvesting system on the bottom

139
00:08:44,066 --> 00:08:46,538
through a breaker.

140
00:08:47,968 --> 00:08:50,770
Now let's look at the products 
for vermicomposting.

141
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:54,628
As the feed passes through 
the earthworm gut,

142
00:08:54,628 --> 00:08:59,815
the material is mineralized,
and plant nutrients are made available.

143
00:08:59,815 --> 00:09:04,545
The grinding effect of the gut
leads to the formation of small granules.

144
00:09:04,545 --> 00:09:08,627
That is quite typical when you take 
vermicompost into your hands,

145
00:09:08,627 --> 00:09:11,041
you see those granules.

146
00:09:11,041 --> 00:09:15,325
Nitrogen content of vermicompost
is typically higher than compost.

147
00:09:15,325 --> 00:09:17,658
It's around one to two percent

148
00:09:17,658 --> 00:09:21,039
and the nutrients 
are easily available to plants.

149
00:09:21,469 --> 00:09:25,826
Furthermore, the enzymes 
in microorganisms from the gut

150
00:09:25,826 --> 00:09:32,206
are also very beneficial for soil
and plants, even suppressing diseases.

151
00:09:32,686 --> 00:09:36,981
Leachate from the worm bins
can also be used as a liquid fertilizer.

152
00:09:36,981 --> 00:09:40,128
This is typically used 
in small scale systems

153
00:09:40,128 --> 00:09:42,228
and they call this <i>Worm Tea.</i>

154
00:09:42,888 --> 00:09:47,164
Earthworms are rich in protein
up to 65%,

155
00:09:47,249 --> 00:09:49,381
with all essential amino acids.

156
00:09:49,381 --> 00:09:55,259
They are considered a good probiotic feed
for fish or for poultry.

157
00:09:55,294 --> 00:09:59,011
In the last 10 years, 
earthworms have also been studied

158
00:09:59,011 --> 00:10:01,165
with regard to their medicinal properties.

159
00:10:01,732 --> 00:10:06,811
What researchers agree on
is their anti-blot clotting effect.

160
00:10:06,811 --> 00:10:10,775
So they were found to be effective
in treating thrombotic diseases.

161
00:10:11,505 --> 00:10:16,158
Worms are also finding new uses 
as a source of collagen

162
00:10:16,158 --> 00:10:18,348
for pharmaceutical industries.

163
